rtac68uConfig.name: rtac68uConfig

revisions.description: The initial version of Asus RT-AC68U.

rtac68uConfig.description: The MIB module of Asus RT-AC68U.

ssidWl2g.name: ssidWl2g
ssidWl2g.description: The network name or SSID is a unique name that identifies the wireless network. WiFi devices automatically detect all networks within range. Assign an identification string of up to 32 characters for your wireless connection.

hideSSIDWl2g.name: hideSSIDWl2g
hideSSIDWl2g.description: If [YES] is selected, your SSID does not show in site surveys by wireless mobile clients and they can only connect to your ASUS Wireless Router with your SSID of AP.

wirelessModeWl2g.name: wirelessModeWl2g
wirelessModeWl2g.description: This item allows you to select any of these options for the Wireless Mode of your 802.11n interface. [Auto]: Allows 802.11n, 802.11g, and 802.11b devices to connect to RT-AC68U. [Legacy]: Allows 802.11b/g/n devices to connect to RT-AC68U, but 802.11n devices only run at a speed of 54Mbps. [n Only]: Maximizes performance, but does not allow 802.11g and 802.11b devices to connect to your device.

protectionWl2g.name: protectionWl2g
protectionWl2g.description: Tick b/g Protection to allow b/g devices to connect to RT-AC68U without affecting 11n devices, but this increases the router's workload.

channelBandwidthWl2g.name: channelBandwidthWl2g
channelBandwidthWl2g.description: Selecting a wider channel bandwidth provides you with a higher transmission speed. Uses 40MHz coexistent bandwidth to maximize the wireless throughput. If you experience issues with wireless stability, please choose the default mode (20MHz).

controlChannelWl2g.name: controlChannelWl2g
controlChannelWl2g.description: The radio channel for wireless connection operation. 0: auto

extensionChannelWl2g.name: extensionChannelWl2g
extensionChannelWl2g.description: Select the extension channel used in the 20/40MHz channel bandwidth mode. 802.11n uses the extension channel to get extra speed. For channels 1 to 4, you can only select an upper channel. For channels 5 to 7, you can select a lower or an upper channel as the extension channel. For channels above 7, you can only select a lower channel.

authenticationWl2g.name: authenticationWl2g
authenticationWl2g.description: This field enables the authentication methods for wireless clients.

wepEncryptionWl2g.name: wepEncryptionWl2g
wepEncryptionWl2g.description: Enable WEP Encyption to encrypt data.

passphraseWl2g.name: passphraseWl2g
passphraseWl2g.description: If you select WEP Encryption, you can key in some words in this field to generate WEP keys automatically.

wpaEncryptionWl2g.name: wpaEncryptionWl2g
wpaEncryptionWl2g.description: Enable WPA Encryption to encrypt data.

wpaPreSharedKeyWl2g.name: wpaPreSharedKeyWl2g
wpaPreSharedKeyWl2g.description: This field requires a password of 8 and 63 characters(letters, numbers or a combination) or 64 hex digits to start the encryption process .

keyRotationIntervalWl2g.name: keyRotationIntervalWl2g
keyRotationIntervalWl2g.description: This field specifies the interval (in seconds) after which a WPA group key is changed . Enter [0] (zero) to indicate that a periodic key-change is not required.

enableWPSWl2g.name: enableWPSWl2g
enableWPSWl2g.description: Selecting Yes allows Wi-Fi Protected Setup (WPS) to simplify the process of connecting any device to the wireless network. WPS support the authentication of Open system, WPA-Personal, WPA2-Personal. Not support Shared Key, WPA-Enterprise, WPA2-Enterprise and Radius.

switchFrequencyTo5g.name: switchFrequencyTo5g
switchFrequencyTo5g.description: If [YES] is selected, frequency of WPS will be switched to 5G. This value can be set only when WPS is disabled.

apPinCodeWl2g.name: apPinCodeWl2g
apPinCodeWl2g.description: Key in the router's PIN code in the client's WPS utility and configure the network name and security settings.

wpsMethodWl2g.name: wpsMethodWl2g
wpsMethodWl2g.description: Selecting PIN (Personal Information Number) you have to enter a number to establish a wireless connection. Select PBC (Push Button Configuration) you have to push a button to establish a wireless connection.

wbApModeWl2g.name: wbApModeWl2g
wbApModeWl2g.description: Select [AP Only] to disable Wireless Bridge function. Select [WDS Only] to disable local wireless station connection. Select [Hybrid] to enable Wireless bridge function and wireless stations will be able to connect to the AP.

wbConnectRemoteBridegeAPWl2g.name: wbConnectRemoteBridegeAPWl2g
wbConnectRemoteBridegeAPWl2g.description: Select [Yes] to connect RT-AC68U to other APs listed in the Remote AP List.

wbAPResultBSSIDWl2g.name: wbAPResultBSSIDWl2g
wbAPResultBSSIDWl2g.description: BSSID of the AP scan result.

wbAPResultSSIDWl2g.name: wbAPResultSSIDWl2g
wbAPResultSSIDWl2g.description: SSID of the AP scan result.

wbRemoteAPMACAddrWl2g.name: wbRemoteAPMACAddrWl2g
wbRemoteAPMACAddrWl2g.description: MAC address of remote bridge APs.

macFilterModeWl2g.name: macFilterModeWl2g
macFilterModeWl2g.description: In Accept mode, RT-AC68U only accept clients with MAC address in the list. In Reject mode, RT-AC68U will reject clients with MAC address in the list.

macFilterMACAddrWl2g.name: macFilterMACAddrWl2g
macFilterMACAddrWl2g.description: MAC address of station which device controls its access.

radiusServerIPAddrWl2g.name: radiusServerIPAddrWl2g
radiusServerIPAddrWl2g.description: The IP address of the RADIUS server for wireless authentication and dynamic WEP key derivation.

radiusPortWl2g.name: radiusPortWl2g
radiusPortWl2g.description: The UDP port number for connection to the RADIUS server.

radiusConnectionSecretWl2g.name: radiusConnectionSecretWl2g
radiusConnectionSecretWl2g.description: The password to connect to the RADIUS server.

enableSchedWl2g.name: enableSchedWl2g
enableSchedWl2g.description: Select [Yes] to enable wirelss schedule function.

weekDaysEnableRadioWl2g.name: weekDaysEnableRadioWl2g
weekDaysEnableRadioWl2g.description: This field defines the dates that wireless function is enabled.

weekDaysRadioStartTimeHWl2g.name: weekDaysRadioStartTimeHWl2g
weekDaysRadioStartTimeHWl2g.description: Hour of starting time of weekdays to enable 2.4G radio.

weekDaysRadioStartTimeMWl2g.name: weekDaysRadioStartTimeMWl2g
weekDaysRadioStartTimeMWl2g.description: Minute of starting time of weekdays to enable 2.4G radio.

weekDaysRadioEndTimeHWl2g.name: weekDaysRadioEndTimeHWl2g
weekDaysRadioEndTimeHWl2g.description: Hour of ending time of weekdays to enable 2.4G radio.

weekDaysRadioEndTimeMWl2g.name: weekDaysRadioEndTimeMWl2g
weekDaysRadioEndTimeMWl2g.description: Minute of ending time of weekdays to enable 2.4G radio.

weekendEnableRadioWl2g.name: weekendEnableRadioWl2g
weekendEnableRadioWl2g.description: This field defines the dates that wireless function is enabled.

weekendRadioStartTimeHWl2g.name: weekendRadioStartTimeHWl2g
weekendRadioStartTimeHWl2g.description: Hour of starting time of weekend to enable 2.4G radio.

weekendRadioStartTimeMWl2g.name: weekendRadioStartTimeMWl2g
weekendRadioStartTimeMWl2g.description: Minute of starting time of weekend to enable 2.4G radio.

weekendRadioEndTimeHWl2g.name: weekendRadioEndTimeHWl2g
weekendRadioEndTimeHWl2g.description: Hour of ending time of weekend to enable 2.4G radio.

weekendRadioEndTimeMWl2g.name: weekendRadioEndTimeMWl2g
weekendRadioEndTimeMWl2g.description: Minute of ending time of weekend to enable 2.4G radio.

apIsolatedWl2g.name: apIsolatedWl2g
apIsolatedWl2g.description: When this feature is enabled, wireless clients or devices will not be able to communicate with each other. You may want to utilize this feature if you have many guests that frequent your wireless network.

roamingAssistantWl2g.name: roamingAssistantWl2g
roamingAssistantWl2g.description: In multiple AP or wireless router-repeater environment, client sometimes cannot automatically connect to the AP with better signal because it still connect to main wireless router. Enabling this feature would force disconnecting the client and main router when the signal strength is under the threshold and client can choose the AP with better signal.

disconnectClientRSSIWl2g.name: disconnectClientRSSIWl2g
disconnectClientRSSIWl2g.description: Disconnect clients with RSSI lower than the settings.

igmpSnoopingWl2g.name: igmpSnoopingWl2g
igmpSnoopingWl2g.description: When enabled, IGMP Snooping monitors IGMP communication among devices and optimizes wireless multicast traffic.

multicastRateWl2g.name: multicastRateWl2g
multicastRateWl2g.description: Select the multicast transmission rate. You are recommended to select Auto to maximize performance.

preambleTypeWl2g.name: preambleTypeWl2g
preambleTypeWl2g.description: The Preamble type defines the length of the CRC (Cyclic Redundancy Check) block, which is a technique for detecting data transmission errors among wireless devices. We recommend that you configure all wireless devices to the same preamble type. Use short preamble for wireless devices in high network traffic areas. Use long preamble for older wireless devices.

aMPDURTSWl2g.name: aMPDURTSWl2g
aMPDURTSWl2g.description: Select 'Enable' to use RTS for every AMPDU.

rtsThresholdWl2g.name: rtsThresholdWl2g
rtsThresholdWl2g.description: Lower the signal RTS (Request To Send) to promote the transmission efficiency in condition of noisy environment or too many clients.

dtimIntervalWl2g.name: dtimIntervalWl2g
dtimIntervalWl2g.description: DTIM (Delivery Traffic Indication Message) is included in Beacon packet.The DTIM Interval (1-255) means the period of time to wake up wireless clients from Sleep Mode. The default value is 3.

beaconIntervalWl2g.name: beaconIntervalWl2g
beaconIntervalWl2g.description: Beacon Interval means the period of time between one beacon and the next one. The default value is 100 (the unit is millisecond, or 1/1000 second). Lower the Beacon Interval to improve transmission performance in unstable environment or for roaming clients, but it will be power consuming.

txBurstingWl2g.name: txBurstingWl2g
txBurstingWl2g.description: Selecting [Enable] enables TX Bursting to improve the transmission speed (from AP to client) of g devices.

wmmAPSDWl2g.name: wmmAPSDWl2g
wmmAPSDWl2g.description: Enable or Disable WMM APSD (Automatic Power Save Delivery).

optimizeAMPDUAggregWl2g.name: optimizeAMPDUAggregWl2g
optimizeAMPDUAggregWl2g.description: Optimize max number of mpdus in an AMDPU.

optimizeAckSuppressionWl2g.name: optimizeAckSuppressionWl2g
optimizeAckSuppressionWl2g.description: Optimize max number of ack to suppress in a row.

txPowerAdjustmentWl2g.name: txPowerAdjustmentWl2g
txPowerAdjustmentWl2g.description: Increase Tx Power to enhance the transmission quality or decrease Tx Power to reduce power consumption.

fragThresholdWl5g.description: Fragmentation Threshold sets the frame size of incoming messages (ranging from 256 to 2346 bytes) used as fragmentation boundary. If the frame size is too big, the heavy interference affects transmission reliability. If the frame size is too small, it decreases transmission efficiency.

wmmNoAcknowledgementWl5g.description: [No-Acknowledgement] is the acknowledge policy at MAC level. When enabled, it results in more efficient throughput but higher error rates in a noisy Radio Frequency (RF) environment.

explicitBeamformingWl5g.name: explicitBeamformingWl5g
explicitBeamformingWl5g.description: The client's WLAN adapter and router both support beamforming technology. This technology allows these devices to communicate the channel estimation and steering direction to each other to improve download and uplink speed.

txPowerAdjustmentWl5g.name: txPowerAdjustmentWl5g
txPowerAdjustmentWl5g.description: Increase Tx Power to enhance the transmission quality or decrease Tx Power to reduce power consumption.

lIPAddress.name: lIPAddress
lIPAddress.description: The value of this object is IP Address of the device as seen in your local network. The default value is 192.168.1.1.

lSubnetMask.name: lSubnetMask
lSubnetMask.description: The value this object is Subnet Mask of the device as seen in your local network. The default value is 255.255.255.0.

enableDHCPServer.name: enableDHCPServer
enableDHCPServer.description: Enable the DHCP server function to allow the router's DHCP server to automatically assign IP addresses to network clients. If this function is disabled, you need to manually assign the IP address settings on your LAN devices.

domainName.name: domainName
domainName.description: The Domain Name for clients who request IP Address from the DHCP Server.

ipPoolStartingAddress.name: ipPoolStartingAddress
ipPoolStartingAddress.description: The first address in the pool to be assigned by the DHCP server in LAN.

ipPoolEndingAddress.name: ipPoolEndingAddress
ipPoolEndingAddress.description: This field indicates the last address in the pool to be assigned by the DHCP server in LAN.

leaseTime.name: leaseTime
leaseTime.description: Set the lease time that the network client is allowed to use its current IP address to connect to the wireless router. When the lease time expires, the network client should either renew or get a new IP address from the wireless router's DHCP server.

defaultGateway.name: defaultGateway
defaultGateway.description: This field indicates the IP address of gateway in your LAN. If you leave it blank, the IP address of RT-AC68U will be assigned.

dnsServer.name: dnsServer
dnsServer.description: This field indicates the IP address of DNS to provide to clients that request IP Address from DHCP Server. You can leave it blank, then the DNS request will be processed by RT-AC68U.

winsServer.name: winsServer
winsServer.description: The Windows Internet Naming Service manages interaction of each PC with the Internet. If you use a WINS server, enter IP Address of server here.

enableManualAssignment.name: enableManualAssignment
enableManualAssignment.description: Assign a fixed IP address for a specific client. The client's MAC address is required.

dsClientMACAddr.name: dsClientMACAddr
dsClientMACAddr.description: MAC address of the client list.

dsClientIPAddr.name: dsClientIPAddr
dsClientIPAddr.description: IP address of the client list.

assignedIPTable.name: assignedIPTable
assignedIPTable.description: Assigned IP around the DHCP list.

assignedIPMACAddr.name: assignedIPMACAddr
assignedIPMACAddr.description: MAC address of assigned IP around the DHCP list.

assignedIPIPAddr.name: assignedIPIPAddr
assignedIPIPAddr.description: IP address of assigned IP around the DHCP list.

rClientIPAddr.name: rClientIPAddr
rClientIPAddr.description: IP address of the client list.

staticRouteIPAddr.name: staticRouteIPAddr
staticRouteIPAddr.description: IP address of static route list.

iptvSTBPort.name: iptvSTBPort
iptvSTBPort.description: This variable can be set only when the value of 'selectISPProfile' is 'none'.

internetVID.name: internetVID
internetVID.description: User can set this variable only when 'selectISPProfile' is 'manual'. Blank value means internetVID won't be used. Value Range: 2-4094.

internetPRIO.name: internetPRIO
internetPRIO.description: User can set this variable only when 'selectISPProfile' is 'manual'.

lan4PortVID.name: lan4PortVID
lan4PortVID.description: User can set this variable only when 'selectISPProfil'e is 'manual'. Blank value means internetVID won't be used. Value Range: 2-4094.

lan4PortPRIO.name: lan4PortPRIO
lan4PortPRIO.description: User can set this variable only when 'selectISPProfile' is 'manual'.

lan3PortVID.name: lan3PortVID
lan3PortVID.description: User can set this variable only when 'selectISPProfile' is 'manual'. Blank value means internetVID won't be used. Value Range: 2-4094.

lan3PortPRIO.name: lan3PortPRIO
lan3PortPRIO.description: User can set this variable only when 'selectISPProfile' is 'manual'.

enableMulticastRouting.name: enableMulticastRouting
enableMulticastRouting.description: Allows the wireless router to handle the multicast packets. Enabling multicast router also enables the RTP and RTSP functions.

udpProxy.name: udpProxy
udpProxy.description: Use this function to run the IPTV application (such as VLC) on several computers at the same time. This function can convert multicast UDP streams to unicast HTTP streams. Enter the port (such as 4000) that you want to assign for the IPTV application, then use this format to enter the address in the play list to watch IPTV streams: http://[Router IP]: [Udpxy port]/[protocol]/[channel IP address]:[channel port] (such as http://192.168.1.1: 4000/udp/239.255.1.1:5000 or http://192.168.1.1:4000/rtp/239.255.1.2:5000). Enter 0 (zero) to disable this function.

wenableNAT.name: wenableNAT
wenableNAT.description: NAT (Network Address Translation) is a process used in routers to replace the address information of network packet with new address information. Typical applications for NAT is router which connect to LAN with the WAN. In LAN every network devices had a private IP(LAN IP) but there is only one public IP(WAN IP). To grant the network devices access to the Internet, the router replaces the private IP address of the sender with its own public IP address in all outgoing data packets. The router saves all necessary information in a table(NAT table) so that incoming data packets can then be assigned on the correct network device.

wenableUPnP.name: wenableUPnP
wenableUPnP.description: UPnP (Universal Plug and Play) allows several devices (routers, televisions, stereo systems, game consoles, cellular phone) to be controlled via an IP-based network with or without a central control through a gateway.

wwIPAddress.name: wwIPAddress

lenableNAT.name: lenableNAT
lenableNAT.description: NAT (Network Address Translation) is a process used in routers to replace the address information of network packet with new address information. Typical applications for NAT is router which connect to LAN with the WAN. In LAN every network devices had a private IP(LAN IP) but there is only one public IP(WAN IP). To grant the network devices access to the Internet, the router replaces the private IP address of the sender with its own public IP address in all outgoing data packets. The router saves all necessary information in a table(NAT table) so that incoming data packets can then be assigned on the correct network device.

operationMode.name: operationMode
operationMode.description: RT-AC68U supports several operation modes to meet different requirements. Please select the mode that match your situation. * In wireless router/ IP sharing mode, RT-AC68U connects to the Internet via PPPoE, DHCP, PPTP, L2TP, or Static IP and shares the wireless network to LAN clients or devices. In this mode, NAT, firewall, and DHCP server are enabled by default. UPnP and Dynamic DNS are supported for SOHO and home users. Select this mode if you are a first-time user or you are not currently using any wired/wireless routers. * In Repeater mode, RT-AC68U wirelessly connects to an existing wireless network to extend the wireless coverage. In this mode, the firewall, IP sharing, and NAT functions are disabled. * In Access Point (AP) mode, RT-AC68U connects to a wireless router through an Ethernet cable to extend the wireless signal coverage to other network clients. In this mode, the firewall, IP sharing, and NAT functions are disabled by default. * RT-AC68U can be configured in Media bridge mode.The Media Bridge mode provides the fastest 802.11ac Wi-Fi connection for multiple media devices simultaneously. To set up the Media Bridge mode, you need two RT-AC68U: one configured as the Media station and the other as a router.Configure one RT-AC68U as a router and another RT-AC68U as an 802.11ac Media bridge to provide a simultaneous 802.11ac Wi-Fi connection for your media devices such as computer, Smart TV, game console, DVR, or media player via Ethernet cable.Change to Media Bridge mode to provide a simultaneous 802.11ac Wi-Fi connection for your media devices. In media bridge mode, only wireless devices connect to the P-AP. Client devices need to be connected to the media bridge with a network cable.
